<h3 class="mbs-4">Fallback</h3>
<p>
  If a font doesn't support a particular script, the browser
  will fall back to a font that does. We can get ahead of
  this by specifying a fallback font in our CSS. The
  following uses the Impact font with no fallback. Note how
  non-Latin glyphs fall back to the system font.
</p>
